"[\n  \"BREAKING: Interior Ministry confirms 14 fatalities at Charlie Hebdo HQ, including editor Charb. Gunmen fled towards Porte de Vincennes.\",\n  \"Official update: Police have identified the Kouachi brothers as primary suspects in the Paris attack. A manhunt is underway in Aisne.\",\n  \"Confirmed by AFP: Two police officers killed outside Charlie Hebdo offices. Shooter shouted 'Allahu Akbar' before fleeing in a black Citroën.\",\n  \"DGSI source states the attackers were trained in Yemen by AQAP. They carried AK-47s and rocket launchers during the siege.\",\n  \"Just in: The satirical magazine had received specific threats from ISIS last month regarding the recent Prophet cartoons publication.\",\n  \"Witnesses report three gunmen entered the building at 11:30 AM. One remained outside as lookout near Rue Nicolas-Appert.\",\n  \"Emergency services confirm no survivors among the editorial staff found on the 2nd floor. Total casualty count now stands at 12.\",\n  \"Police spokesperson announces the recovery of an ID card dropped by one attacker near the scene, linking him to prior terror watchlists.\",\n  \"Update: The alleged getaway driver, Hamyd Mourad, has surrendered to authorities in Charleville-Mézières this morning.\",\n  \"French intelligence intercepted communications between the shooters and a known radical cleric in the 19th arrondissement yesterday.\",\n  \"Ministry of Justice confirms that the attackers had been flagged for radicalization in 2010 but released due to lack of evidence.\",\n  \"Live feed: Sniper teams positioned on rooftops surrounding the Dammartin-en-Goële warehouse where suspects are currently barricaded.\"\n]"